  "chapter": {
    "number": 4,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Answer Me When I Call!"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "hebrew_subtitle",
        "content": [
          "For the choirmaster. With stringed instruments. A Psalm of David."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Answer me when I call,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O God of my righteousness!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You have relieved my distress;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "show me grace and hear my prayer.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How long, O men, will my honor be maligned?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "How long will you love vanity and seek after lies",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4280
          },
          {
            "text": "?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "Selah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Know that the LORD has set apart the godly for Himself;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD hears when I call to Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Be angry, yet do not sin;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4281
          },
          {
            "text": "on your bed, search your heart and be still.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "Selah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Offer the sacrifices of the righteous",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and trust in the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Many ask, “Who can show us the good?”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Shine the light of Your face upon us, O LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have filled my heart with more joy",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than when grain and new wine abound.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will lie down and sleep in peace,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for You alone, O LORD, make me dwell in safety.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 4280,
        "caller": "+",
